From: audiocore contributors
Subject: [PATCH] qwen3: pass n_embd_k_gqa (not n_embd_gqa) for the K/V
 weight dimension in create_tensor_qkv

create_tensor_qkv's 5th argument is the per-head K/V dimension, which is
n_embd_k_gqa (= n_embd_head_k * n_head). The current code passes
n_embd_gqa (= n_embd / kv_head_count) which is only correct when
n_embd_head_k happens to equal n_embd / n_head. For Qwen3-TTS Talker
(heads=16, kv_heads=8) this is wrong and the loaded weight shape does
not match the architecture.

Upstream-Status: Pending
---
 src/models/qwen3.cpp | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/models/qwen3.cpp b/src/models/qwen3.cpp
--- a/src/models/qwen3.cpp
+++ b/src/models/qwen3.cpp
@@ -33,7 +33,7 @@ void llama_model_qwen3::load_arch_tensors(llama_model_loader &) {
 
         layer.attn_norm = create_tensor(tn(LLM_TENSOR_ATTN_NORM, "weight", i), {n_embd}, 0);
 
-        create_tensor_qkv(layer, i, n_embd, n_embd_head_k * n_head, n_embd_gqa, n_embd_gqa, 0);
+        create_tensor_qkv(layer, i, n_embd, n_embd_head_k * n_head, n_embd_k_gqa, n_embd_gqa, 0);
         layer.wo = create_tensor(tn(LLM_TENSOR_ATTN_OUT, "weight", i), {n_embd_head_k * n_head, n_embd}, 0);
 
         layer.attn_k_norm = create_tensor(tn(LLM_TENSOR_ATTN_K_NORM, "weight", i), {n_embd_head_k}, 0);

